## Summary

Added the in-memory checkpoint infrastructure for graph snapshot isolation
(ADR-035). `CheckpointId` is a monotonic u64 newtype (id 0 reserved as
NONE). `VersionedGraphCache` is a `VecDeque`-backed ring with FIFO
retention. `GraphCache` was refactored to wrap
`ArcSwap<Mutex<VersionedGraphCache>>` so writes can publish a new head
while in-flight readers pin to an older version. The default retention
is 2 (current + previous). All 18 graph_cache tests and 11 new
checkpoint tests pass; no existing tests were broken by the refactor
(the 4 pre-existing lib test failures are PG/manifest-related and
unrelated to GraphCache).

